The national leader of Afenifere has congratulated President Muhammadu Buhari on his victory at the Presidential Election Petition Tribunal in Abuja.
Chief Abiodun Akin-Fasae, Afenifere Publicity Secretary in Ekiti, who spoke on behalf of the leader Ayo Fasanmi, said on Wednesday that the president’s victory was a good development for Nigerians and democracy.
Fasanmi commended the judiciary ” for painstakingly going through the details of the petition without bothering whose ox was gored.”
He advised all petitioners and stakeholders to come together and work for the progress of the country, saying ” there is opportunity for everyone at all times to contribute to its development.”
The PDP and its candidate Atiku Abubakar, however,  are not taking the loss at the tribunal lightly.
The party vowed to take ts case to the Supreme Court to address the what he it described as subversion of justice at the tribunal.

			
